1082
01:16:55,278 --> 01:16:58,256
波士顿海岸警卫队 这里是Unimak号
Coast Guard Boston, this is the Unimak.

1083
01:16:58,281 --> 01:16:59,788
我们现在已到Mercer号船头
We're at the Mercer bow now,

1084
01:16:59,817 --> 01:17:01,399
有Yakutat号支援
here in support of the Yakutat.

1085
01:17:01,424 --> 01:17:03,986
四名Mercer号船员从甲板跳下海
Four Mercer crew men jumped from the deck,

1086
01:17:04,015 --> 01:17:05,220
均已失联
all were lost.

1087
01:17:05,245 --> 01:17:07,157
再说一遍 四人失联
Repeat, four men lost.

1088
01:17:07,182 --> 01:17:09,807
有些船员出现了低温症
Several crew members have hypothermia.

1089
01:17:09,832 --> 01:17:14,699
天亮后我们再开始新一轮营救 完毕
We're gonna for daybreak to attempt another rescue. Over.

1090
01:17:15,796 --> 01:17:18,716
听这些没什么好处 Miriam
Does no good listenin' to all that chatter, Miriam...

1091
01:17:18,741 --> 01:17:21,473
学会充耳不闻比较好
better learnin'to live not knowin'.

1092
01:17:25,352 --> 01:17:28,531
大约晚上七点 我们...
at roughly 1900 hours we...

1093
01:17:32,352 --> 01:17:36,320
- 你和Bernie结婚多久了 - 我们...
- How long you been married to Bernie for? - We're...

1094
01:17:40,108 --> 01:17:42,623
我们还没结婚
We're not married yet.

1095
01:17:44,529 --> 01:17:45,624
我不知道是不是...
I didn't know if I...

1096
01:17:45,649 --> 01:17:49,193
我说过 Bernie是个好人
Like I said, Bernie, he's a good man.

1097
01:17:52,036 --> 01:17:54,318
一年前 他和其他人试图出海
Him and some of them others try gettin' out a year ago,

1098
01:17:54,343 --> 01:17:56,723
营救我丈夫Arnie和Landry号上的船员
save my husband Arnie and the crew of the Landry.

1099
01:17:56,748 --> 01:17:59,011
他们当时在南塔基特湾附近捕马林鱼
They were out fishin' marlin near Nantucket Sound

1100
01:17:59,036 --> 01:18:00,325
船进了水
when the boat started takin' on water,

1101
01:18:00,354 --> 01:18:01,770
也是像这样的一个夜晚
A night just like this.

1102
01:18:03,213 --> 01:18:06,106
来吧 我们要走了
Come on, we gotta get goin'.

1103
01:18:06,131 --> 01:18:07,633
我哥在来的路上了
Brother's on his way to come meet us.

1104
01:18:07,658 --> 01:18:10,595
我得去寄宿站了 你们俩过来
I gotta get down to the lodge, come on, you two.

1105
01:18:42,680 --> 01:18:45,319
# 大家都叫你坐下 #
For the people all said sit down

1106
01:18:45,400 --> 01:18:47,356
# 坐下吧 你让船晃个不停 #
Sit down, you're rockin' the boat

1107
01:18:48,720 --> 01:18:51,314
# 大家都叫你坐下 #
For the people all said sit down

1108
01:18:51,480 --> 01:18:53,516
# 坐下吧 你让船晃个不停 #
Sit down, you're rockin ' the boat

1109
01:18:53,680 --> 01:18:56,478
# 魔鬼会拉着你的花格外套尖衣领 #
And the devil may pull you under

1110
01:18:56,640 --> 01:18:59,313
# 把你拖入水底 #
By the sharp lapels of your checkered coat

1111
01:19:09,160 --> 01:19:10,513
# 坐下吧 坐下吧 #
Sit down, sit down, sit dow

1112
01:19:55,094 --> 01:19:57,179
你知道她是谁吗
Do you know who she is?

1113
01:19:57,840 --> 01:20:00,381
Carly 不是Bernie的错 不是任何人的错
Ain't Bernie's fault, Carly, nobody's fault,

1114
01:20:00,406 --> 01:20:02,890
不然她也能怪你
Be like her blaming you.

1115
01:20:03,187 --> 01:20:04,622
为什么怪我
For what?

1116
01:20:04,647 --> 01:20:06,412
是你告诉他们那里还有一艘船
You're the one that told them there's another ship out there,

1117
01:20:06,437 --> 01:20:09,031
所以他们才出海的 对吧
they're out there because of you, right?

1118
01:21:25,117 --> 01:21:29,015
Fitz 打开探照灯
Fitz, turn on the searchlight.

1119
01:22:16,720 --> 01:22:20,313
难以置信 我们竟然找到了 快看
I can't believe we found her, look at that!

1120
01:22:23,478 --> 01:22:28,017
我们来迟了 船上没人了
We're too late, she's a ghost ship.

1121
01:22:31,146 --> 01:22:34,230
- 你看到了吗 长官 - 看到了
- Are you seeing this, Sir? - Yeah.

1122
01:22:34,300 --> 01:22:35,350
- 你看到那个人了吗 - 是的 我看到了
- You see that guy? - Yeah, yeah, I see him.

1123
01:22:36,377 --> 01:22:38,911
真不敢相信
Not sure I believe it.

1124
01:22:41,582 --> 01:22:44,417
他这是去哪儿了
Where is the hell's he goin'?

1125
01:22:51,918 --> 01:22:54,660
见到你们太好了
Good to see you, boys.

1126
01:23:00,528 --> 01:23:02,965
小心
Careful.

1127
01:23:08,782 --> 01:23:11,127
我们这船怎么装得下他们所有人
How we gonna fit them all on this boat?

1128
01:23:11,152 --> 01:23:14,508
这船只能载十二个人 包括我们在内
We're only built to hold 12, including us.

1129
01:23:15,265 --> 01:23:18,485
那只是规定 对吧
That's just regulation though, right?

1130
01:23:21,672 --> 01:23:24,054
实际可以装多少人
How many could he fit?

1131
01:23:24,566 --> 01:23:26,968
二十个 最多二十二
Twenty, twenty-two tops.

1132
01:23:28,931 --> 01:23:29,940
等等
Wait.

1133
01:23:29,965 --> 01:23:32,235
他们要下来了
They comin' down here.

1134
01:23:55,696 --> 01:23:58,156
放下支柱 在左舷
Drop the stanchion Port side.

1135
01:24:22,640 --> 01:24:23,640
快过来
Come on!

1136
01:24:28,117 --> 01:24:30,562
来 我拉住你
Come on, I gotcha.

1137
01:24:51,111 --> 01:24:52,704
我们接着你
We got ya.

1138
01:25:02,082 --> 01:25:04,230
Maske 这边
Maske, get over here!

1139
01:25:05,920 --> 01:25:08,847
快 拉住他
Come on! Grab him!

1140
01:25:25,531 --> 01:25:28,039
知道要去哪里吗 小姐
You know where you goin' now, Miss?

1141
01:25:28,438 --> 01:25:30,360
应该知道
I think so.

1142
01:25:30,708 --> 01:25:32,398
谢谢你的帮助 Nickerson先生
Thanks for your help, Mr. Nickerson.

1143
01:25:32,423 --> 01:25:33,399
不谢
Yeah.

1144
01:25:34,362 --> 01:25:35,242
你知道
You know...

1145
01:25:36,923 --> 01:25:38,874
Bernie不是因为我才出海的
Bernie ain't out there, 'cause of me.

1146
01:25:38,899 --> 01:25:40,063
是的 我知道
Yeah, I know.

1147
01:25:41,388 --> 01:25:43,750
这是他的职责 不是吗
It's Bernie's job to go out, right?

1148
01:25:47,195 --> 01:25:49,250
我怎么会怪你呢
How can I blame you for it?

1149
01:26:04,298 --> 01:26:07,074
慢慢来 慢慢来 你可以的
Nice and slow! Nice and slow! You'll be all right.

1150
01:26:07,099 --> 01:26:08,795
Pete 你是下一个
Pete, you're next.

1151
01:26:08,820 --> 01:26:12,665
- 慢慢来 别着急 - 来吧
- Take it nice and slow! Easy! Easy! - Come on.

1152
01:26:20,209 --> 01:26:22,694
你也走吧 大家都得走
You gotta go! We're leavin' nobody behind.

1153
01:26:22,719 --> 01:26:25,431
- Eldon 顺着梯子下去 - 让他下去
- Eldon, get on that ladder. - Come on, we gotta get him down.

1154
01:26:26,688 --> 01:26:30,091
船倾斜了 得赶紧离开
She's slippin', we gotta get off this ship.

1155
01:26:30,378 --> 01:26:31,746
快点
Hurry!

1156
01:26:31,771 --> 01:26:34,201
Eldon 还好吧
Eldon, how you doin'?

1157
01:26:34,676 --> 01:26:36,467
我很害怕
I'm scared.

1158
01:26:40,250 --> 01:26:41,710
嗯
Well...

1159
01:26:43,382 --> 01:26:45,547
只剩你一个在这里的话 就更害怕了
Gonna be a lot scarier up here without us.

1160
01:26:45,572 --> 01:26:47,523
你得听我说
You gotta listen to me!

1161
01:26:48,207 --> 01:26:50,577
- Eldon - 我们都会下去的 别挤了
- Eldon? - We're all gonna get off, stop pushin'!

1162
01:26:50,602 --> 01:26:52,944
你跟着我就好
You just follow right behind me...

1163
01:26:52,969 --> 01:26:55,625
如果我都能做到 人人都可以
if I can do it, anyone can.

1164
01:27:08,888 --> 01:27:10,600
来吧
Come on.

1165
01:27:25,477 --> 01:27:27,711
抓紧
Hold tight!

1166
01:27:36,429 --> 01:27:39,804
小个 小个 坚持住
Tiny! Tiny! Hold on!

1167
01:28:36,320 --> 01:28:39,140
Eldon Eldon
Eldon, Eldon.

1168
01:28:41,499 --> 01:28:44,921
Eldon 看着我 看着我
Eldon, look at me! Look at me!

1169
01:28:56,862 --> 01:28:59,980
我说跳你就跳 准备好了吗
When I say, "Jump", let go! Ready?

1170
01:29:07,001 --> 01:29:08,399
跳
Jump!

1171
01:29:12,496 --> 01:29:13,980
你还好吗
You okay?

1172
01:29:15,808 --> 01:29:17,324
抓紧
Hold tight.

1173
01:29:22,633 --> 01:29:25,369
船太重了 已经很难掌舵了
They're ridin' so heavy, you can hardly steer.

1174
01:29:25,394 --> 01:29:29,597
他们说甲板上还有七八个人
Sir, they're saying there's still 7 or 8 up there on board.

1175
01:29:29,859 --> 01:29:35,581
要不 我们先把这些人带回去 再回来
Maybe... we take these guys back in... come back out.

1176
01:29:43,647 --> 01:29:47,944
不能丢下他们 那艘船撑不了多久了
Can't leave 'em out here alone, that boat won't last.

1177
01:29:50,098 --> 01:29:52,113
我们要同生共死
We all live or we all die.

1178
01:29:54,764 --> 01:29:55,925
对吗
Right?

1179
01:30:29,889 --> 01:30:33,349
你... 你真是好样的
You... you did good.

1180
01:30:34,400 --> 01:30:37,818
你应该最后一个离开 Sybert先生
You should be the last one off, Mr. Sybert.

1181
01:31:35,743 --> 01:31:37,516
最后一个了
Last man!

1182
01:33:16,918 --> 01:33:21,488
Fitz 关掉探照灯 好吗
Hey Fitz! Turn off that searchlight, yeah?

1183
01:33:45,602 --> 01:33:48,565
我们用无线电联系了McCullough号
We were in radio contact with the McCullough,

1184
01:33:48,590 --> 01:33:51,979
他们说四个人殒命了 其余都获救了
They said they lost 4 men, but saved the rest.

1185
01:33:52,004 --> 01:33:53,944
Pollock Rip号的船长说他们...
The captain of the Pollock Rip sent word that they...

1186
01:33:53,969 --> 01:33:57,150
Cluff先生 是36-500号 是Bernie
Mr. Cluff, it is 36-500, it's Bernie.

1187
01:33:57,175 --> 01:33:59,084
联系上他们了
It's right there on the radio.

1188
01:33:59,127 --> 01:34:02,641
查塔姆站 收到请回答
Station Chatham? Station Chatham, copy?

1189
01:34:03,626 --> 01:34:06,914
CG-36-500号 这是查塔姆站
CG-36-500, this Station Chatham.

1190
01:34:06,939 --> 01:34:08,562
Webber 是你吗
Webber, is that you?

1191
01:34:08,587 --> 01:34:11,516
是的 是我 Bernie
Yes, Sir, it's me. It's Bernie.

1192
01:34:12,227 --> 01:34:15,443
我们从Pendleton号沉船上
We got 32... 32 survivors aboard

1193
01:34:15,468 --> 01:34:18,405
营救了... 三十二名幸存者
from... from the sinkin' Pendleton, Sir.

1194
01:34:18,430 --> 01:34:20,272
查塔姆站 听到了吗
Station Chatham, do you copy?

1195
01:34:20,297 --> 01:34:22,194
36-500号 这里是查塔姆站
36-500, Station Chatham,

1196
01:34:22,219 --> 01:34:25,674
你是说你的船上有三十二名幸存者吗
did you say you have 32 survivors on board?

1197
01:34:25,699 --> 01:34:28,222
他们救了三十二个人
They rescued 'em, they rescued 32 of them.

1198
01:34:28,247 --> 01:34:30,589
是的长官 三十二个
Yes sir, 32.

1199
01:34:30,614 --> 01:34:32,324
我们... 我们的罗盘丢了
We... we... we lost our compass,

1200
01:34:32,353 --> 01:34:34,025
所以不知道现在身在何处
so we don't know where we are,

1201
01:34:34,050 --> 01:34:36,129
但我们会努力回去的
but we're gonna try to make it back home.

1202
01:34:36,154 --> 01:34:37,669
没有罗盘可回不来
Can't get back without a compass.

1203
01:34:37,694 --> 01:34:38,476
尤其在这种天气
Not in this weather.

1204
01:34:38,519 --> 01:34:40,359
他们回不来的
They're not gonna make it back.

1205
01:34:40,926 --> 01:34:42,530
你们的罗盘丢了 Webber
You lost your compass, Webber?

1206
01:34:42,555 --> 01:34:45,795
不行 36-500号 这里是Pollock灯塔船
Negative, 36-500, this is the Pollock lightship,

1207
01:34:45,820 --> 01:34:47,599
不要去岸边
do not proceed to shore.

1208
01:34:47,642 --> 01:34:49,015
我们在Pendleton号
We're 5 miles northeast of

1209
01:34:49,040 --> 01:34:50,968
最后已知位置的东北方五英里处
the Pendleton's last known location.

1210
01:34:50,993 --> 01:34:53,178
到我们这里来 完毕
Proceed to our position. Over.

1211
01:34:53,203 --> 01:34:55,744
CG-36-500号 这里是查塔姆站
CG-36-500, Station Chatham,

1212
01:34:55,769 --> 01:35:00,095
前往Pollock灯塔船 转移所有幸存者 完毕
proceed to Pollock lightship and unload all survivors. Over.

1213
01:35:01,008 --> 01:35:03,227
他们又知道什么
What do they know, right?

1214
01:35:05,087 --> 01:35:06,727
对吧 Richie
Right, Richie?

1215
01:35:07,174 --> 01:35:10,594
CG-36-500号 听到请回答
CG-36-500, do you copy?

1216
01:35:13,281 --> 01:35:15,476
如果他们知道自己的位置
If they know where they are...

1217
01:35:15,934 --> 01:35:16,894
就会说出我的位置
someone tell me where I am

1218
01:35:16,919 --> 01:35:18,483
因为我不知道我们身在何处
'cause I don't know where the hell we are.

1219
01:35:18,508 --> 01:35:20,824
Webber 听到请回答
Webber, do you copy?

1220
01:35:20,849 --> 01:35:23,559
我不想再往外面走了... 不
I'm not headin' out to sea... no.

1221
01:35:23,584 --> 01:35:26,163
这是查塔姆站 听到请回答
This is Station Chatham, do you copy?

1222
01:35:26,188 --> 01:35:29,167
刚把你们从一艘船上救下来
We just got you all off a... off a boat,

1223
01:35:29,192 --> 01:35:29,809
我们不想
so there's no way we're...

1224
01:35:29,834 --> 01:35:31,735
再把你们搁在海上了
we're gonna get you all up there.

1225
01:35:31,778 --> 01:35:34,184
CG-36-500号 这是查塔姆站
CG-36-500, this is Station Chatham.

1226
01:35:34,209 --> 01:35:36,308
Webber 我命令你
Webber, your orders are to proceed

1227
01:35:36,358 --> 01:35:37,688
向东北方向行驶五英里
five miles northeast

1228
01:35:37,713 --> 01:35:40,895
将幸存者转移到Pollock号
and unload all survivors onto the Pollock.

1229
01:35:55,480 --> 01:35:57,842
他好像切断了无线电 Cluff先生
Sounds like there's a cut off his radio, Mr. Cluff...

1230
01:35:58,145 --> 01:36:00,112
他要按自己的方式来
he's going it on his own.

1231
01:36:01,328 --> 01:36:03,378
Bernie Webber
Bernie Webber.

1232
01:36:04,358 --> 01:36:05,574
你料得到吗
What do you know?

1233
01:36:05,599 --> 01:36:07,101
他们要怎么样才回得来
How are they gonna find their way home?

1234
01:36:07,124 --> 01:36:09,631
他肯定关了无线电
He must have shut off the radio.

1235
01:36:11,367 --> 01:36:14,835
- 可怜的人 - 不敢相信怎么会这样
- Poor, poor boys. - I can't believe this is happenin'.

1236
01:36:22,722 --> 01:36:24,870
车上还有东西没拿下来
Some more stuff in the car.

1237
01:36:33,190 --> 01:36:34,947
停电了
The power's out.

1238
01:36:35,728 --> 01:36:39,041
整个城都停电了
The whole town, the power's out.

1239
01:36:39,575 --> 01:36:43,283
- 比去年还糟糕 - 他们回不来了
- It's worse than last year. - They'll never make it.

1240
01:37:00,658 --> 01:37:03,290
咱们去码头吧
Let's get to the pier.

1241
01:37:13,125 --> 01:37:15,921
没有罗盘你们是怎么找到我们的
How did you find us without a compass?

1242
01:37:16,083 --> 01:37:22,570
我们... 只是顺着海流走
We... we just jogged along with the seasonal currents.

1243
01:37:26,375 --> 01:37:28,450
可能比较幸运吧
I think we just got lucky.

1244
01:37:28,475 --> 01:37:31,101
- 是啊 - 是啊
- Yeah. - Yeah...

1245
01:37:33,200 --> 01:37:35,004
幸运
Lucky.

1246
01:37:37,875 --> 01:37:40,554
那你知道怎么回去吗
So, you know how you get home?

1247
01:37:41,000 --> 01:37:43,914
说实话 我也不确定
To be honest with ya, I'm not sure.

1248
01:37:43,958 --> 01:37:47,945
我... 没有听从上级的命令
Just... disobeyed all my ranking officers.

1249
01:37:48,439 --> 01:37:52,046
他们不了解情况 我比他们清楚一些 对吧
They don't know, so I guess I... I'd better, right?

1250
01:37:52,093 --> 01:37:54,700
来的时候风是从左面吹来的
Had the wind on my left goin' out,

1251
01:37:54,725 --> 01:37:59,131
我想 如果一直保持风在右面
Figure if I... . Keep it her on my right,

1252
01:37:59,156 --> 01:38:01,201
方向应该不会错
we oughta be headin' the right direction.

1253
01:38:03,492 --> 01:38:05,188
我们只要跟随岸上的灯光
We just follow the lights onshore,

1254
01:38:05,213 --> 01:38:07,701
跟随岸上的一切灯光
follow all the lights onshore.

1255
01:38:20,292 --> 01:38:23,627
我们都靠你了 船长
Well, we are in your hands, Cap'n.

1256
01:38:32,675 --> 01:38:34,487
大家听着
Listen up.

1257
01:38:38,092 --> 01:38:40,677
我要向岸边前进
I'll put the sea behind us.

1258
01:38:41,833 --> 01:38:45,379
让海水推着我们走 直到找到陆地
Just let it push us along, till we land up somewhere.

1259
01:38:45,404 --> 01:38:47,619
风暴... 风暴在逐渐平息 所以
The storm's... the storm's easing' up, boys, so...

1260
01:38:47,669 --> 01:38:50,595
我们只需找寻岸上的灯光
we just look for the lights on the shore to guide us in.

1261
01:38:50,645 --> 01:38:54,073
即使要走到遥远的Nobska灯塔
Even if we have to go so far as Nobska Point.

1262
01:38:54,098 --> 01:38:57,355
也要往前走 我们一定会找到陆地的
So be it! We just gonna find land!

1263
01:39:00,875 --> 01:39:04,654
今天可是无比漫长的一天 对吧
Been one heck of a long day, right fellas?

1264
01:39:04,983 --> 01:39:08,357
的确如此
Yeah, it sure has!

1265
01:39:10,154 --> 01:39:13,271
但是你们要对我有信心
But don't you give up hope on me now.

1266
01:39:15,091 --> 01:39:18,044
这船不错 会让我们度过难关的
It's a good boat, she'll get us through.

1267
01:39:19,717 --> 01:39:23,590
我们会把你们带回家 我们都会回家
We'll get you home, okay? We're all goin' home.

1268
01:39:24,502 --> 01:39:26,731
我们相信你 船长
We're with you, Skipper.

1269
01:42:50,775 --> 01:42:53,562
大家像她一样把车灯打开
Keep the lights on, like she's doin'!

1270
01:42:53,587 --> 01:42:54,876
快点 开灯
Quick! Turn your lights on!

1271
01:42:54,901 --> 01:42:57,587
大家都把灯打开
Turn on the lights, everyone.

1272
01:42:58,667 --> 01:43:01,462
把灯打开 他们就能看到我们了
More light, so that they can see us.

1273
01:43:50,483 --> 01:43:53,209
看来我们已越过沙洲了
I think we made it over the bar.

1274
01:43:55,917 --> 01:43:59,553
是海潮把我们带过来的
That high tide carried us over!

1275
01:44:00,326 --> 01:44:02,287
看到了吗
You see that?

1276
01:44:23,717 --> 01:44:26,927
Fitz 打开探照灯
Fitz, turn on the searchlight.

1277
01:44:57,675 --> 01:45:01,792
- 看 看到了吗 - 是我们的人吗
- Look, you see that? - Is that our boys!

1278
01:45:13,406 --> 01:45:14,952
是他们吗
Is it them?

1279
01:45:17,450 --> 01:45:19,458
干得漂亮 Bernie
Well done, Bernie!

1280
01:45:19,483 --> 01:45:23,517
- 你做到了 Webber - 干得好 Webber
- You did it, Webber! - Well done, Webber!

1281
01:45:23,542 --> 01:45:27,058
36-500号正在靠近查塔姆码头
36-500 is now docking at the Chatham pier.

1282
01:45:27,083 --> 01:45:30,036
看来有三十二名幸存者 长官 再说一遍
There appear to be 32 survivors, Sir. Repeat,

1283
01:45:30,061 --> 01:45:32,437
共三十二人获救
we have 32 survivors.

1284
01:45:45,800 --> 01:45:47,233
很好
That's right.

1285
01:45:47,360 --> 01:45:48,793
扔过来 孩子
Throw it, son.

1286
01:45:53,228 --> 01:45:55,470
好小子 Bernie
Atta boy! Bernie.

1287
01:46:05,704 --> 01:46:07,102
拉他们一把
Give 'em a hand.

1288
01:46:07,417 --> 01:46:09,352
- 见到你们真好 - 快上来
- Good to see you. - Get on up here.

1289
01:46:09,800 --> 01:46:10,800
慢慢来
Nice and easy.

1290
01:46:10,880 --> 01:46:12,996
还以为再也见不到你们了
We never thought we'd see you again.

1291
01:46:13,000 --> 01:46:14,423
这位要冻僵了 给我件大衣
This man's freezing, get me a coat.

1292
01:46:14,581 --> 01:46:16,792
快进去 里面暖和
Go on in, it's warm inside.

1293
01:46:18,483 --> 01:46:20,729
去寄宿室吧
Let's get you up to the lodge.

1294
01:46:20,800 --> 01:46:22,795
下一位 我抓住你了
Next up. Come on, now. I got you.

1295
01:46:37,525 --> 01:46:39,704
干得好 船长
Good job, Cap'n.

1296
01:46:42,814 --> 01:46:45,040
好样的 Bernie
Way to go, Bernie.

1297
01:46:56,805 --> 01:46:58,180
Webber
Webber?

1298
01:47:25,317 --> 01:47:26,590
Bernie
Bernie.

1299
01:48:06,425 --> 01:48:07,901
我们回家吧
Let's go home.

1300
01:48:41,367 --> 01:48:43,452
我们还是四月十六日结婚吗
Are we still good for April 16th?

1301
01:48:44,218 --> 01:48:46,515
- 是的 - 是的
- Yeah. - Yeah.

1302
01:48:47,308 --> 01:48:49,320
我替你请示过Cluff了
I asked Cluff for ya.

1303
01:48:50,483 --> 01:48:53,546
- 他说这只是一种形式而已 - 形式
- He said it's just a formality. - Formality.

1304
01:48:54,454 --> 01:48:56,937
现在我知道了
Now I know, right?

1305
01:49:06,190 --> 01:49:15,440
伯尼·韦伯 理查德·李甫西 安迪·菲茨杰拉德 和 欧文·马斯基
于1952年2月18日夜晚所完成的壮举
至今仍被誉为海岸警卫队历史上最伟大的小船救援行动

1306
01:49:20,210 --> 01:49:23,670
伯尼和米丽娅姆在选定的日期完婚

1307
01:49:23,670 --> 01:49:29,840
他们的婚姻持续了58年 直至伯尼以81岁的高龄
于2009年去世
伯尼和米丽娅姆在选定的日期完婚

1308
01:49:32,260 --> 01:49:40,130
四位海岸警卫队队员也因这一壮举
获得了金质救生奖章

1309
01:49:40,480 --> 01:49:45,300
怒海救援


